  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Bridge Frequency.}\n\\begin{equation}\nf_{\\mathrm{bridge}}=\\frac{32}{27}f_0.\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Bridge Waveform.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\Psi_{\\mathrm{bridge}}(t)\n=\nG_{\\sigma}(t)\n\\left[\n\\cos(2\\pi f_1t)\n-\n\\cos(2\\pi f_2t+\\theta)\n\\right].\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nLet $f_0$ be a shared base frequency.  \nThe bridge frequency is fixed by:\n\n\\begin{equation}\nf_{\\mathrm{bridge}}=\\frac{32}{27}f_0.\n\\end{equation}\n\nA localized bridge is created by applying a Gaussian window $G_\\sigma(t)$ to a flipped and twisted carrier pair:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\n\\Psi_{\\mathrm{bridge}}(t)\n=\nG_{\\sigma}(t)\n\\left[\n\\cos(2\\pi f_1t)\n-\n\\cos(2\\pi f_2t+\\theta)\n\\right].\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nThe flip--twist transform creates a localized beat-and-cancellation bridge from paired carriers.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
